       <field>
         <dc-schema>dc</dc-schema>
         <dc-element>contributor</dc-element>
         <dc-qualifier>author</dc-qualifier>
         <repeatable>true</repeatable>
         <label>Creators</label>
         <input-type>name</input-type>
         <hint>Enter the names of the creators of the dataset. Use the 'Lookup' button to find people registered in ORCID. Use the 'Add' button for people not registered in ORCID. You can search by name or ORCID ID.</hint>
         <required>Enter the creators of the dataset.</required>
       </field>

       <field>
         <dc-schema>dc</dc-schema>
         <dc-element>description</dc-element>
         <dc-qualifier>abstract</dc-qualifier>
         <repeatable>false</repeatable>
         <input-type>textarea</input-type>
         <label>Description of dataset</label>
         <hint>Enter the abstract of the item. </hint>
         <hint>It is important to describe your dataset as thoroughly as possible so that others can interpret and understand your research. Where possible you should try to include details of: the methodology, how the data was analysed, any software or equipment used to collect or analyse the data, the structure and content of the files included in the dataset. 

Your description should be between 50 and 250 words in length. Detailed descriptions can be included within a ‘readme’ file – preferably in plain text format. For more advice see our guide on the &lt;a href="https://stfc.ent.sirsidynix.net.uk/client/en_GB/library/?rm=MANAGING+YOUR+0%7C%7C%7C1%7C%7C%7C0%7C%7C%7Ctrue" target="_blank"&gt;library webpage&lt;/a&gt;.</hint>
         <required>Enter a description of the dataset.</required>
       </field>

       <field>
         <dc-schema>dc</dc-schema>
         <dc-element>subject</dc-element>
         <dc-qualifier>other</dc-qualifier>
         <!-- An input-type of twobox MUST be marked as repeatable -->
         <repeatable>true</repeatable>
         <label>Subject Keywords</label>
         <input-type>twobox</input-type>
         <hint>Add appropriate subject keywords or phrases that will help make your research more discoverable.</hint>
         <required></required>
       </field>

       <field>
         <dc-schema>dc</dc-schema>
         <dc-element>date</dc-element>
         <dc-qualifier>issued</dc-qualifier>
         <repeatable>false</repeatable>
         <label>Date of Issue</label>
         <input-type>date</input-type>
         <hint>Please give the date of publication or public distribution. You must enter the year at minimum. However, the day and/or month can be left blank if they are not applicable. 

For datasets that are under embargo, please enter the date the embargo will end and the dataset will become publicly available. If you are entering legacy data, please enter the date the dataset first became publicly available. 

 &lt;b&gt;Please Note:&lt;/b&gt; entering a future date into this field &lt;b&gt;will not apply an embargo&lt;/b&gt; to your dataset. This must be done on page 3 of the submission form.  For more advice see our guide on the &lt;a href="https://stfc.ent.sirsidynix.net.uk/client/en_GB/library/?rm=MANAGING+YOUR+0%7C%7C%7C1%7C%7C%7C0%7C%7C%7Ctrue" target="_blank"&gt;library webpage&lt;/a&gt;.</hint>
         <required>You must enter at least the year.</required>
       </field>

       <field>
         <dc-schema>dc</dc-schema>
         <dc-element>type</dc-element>
         <dc-qualifier></dc-qualifier>
         <repeatable>false</repeatable>
         <label>Type</label>
         <input-type value-pairs-name="common_types">dropdown</input-type>
         <hint>Select the type of content of the item(s) uploaded. If more than one type applies, please select &lt;b&gt;collection&lt;/b&gt;.

For definitions of each resource type and more advice see our guide on the &lt;a href="https://stfc.ent.sirsidynix.net.uk/client/en_GB/library/?rm=MANAGING+YOUR+0%7C%7C%7C1%7C%7C%7C0%7C%7C%7Ctrue" target="_blank"&gt;library webpage&lt;/a&gt;.</hint>
         <required></required>
       </field>

       <field>
         <dc-schema>dc</dc-schema>
         <dc-element>language</dc-element>
         <dc-qualifier>iso</dc-qualifier>
         <repeatable>false</repeatable>
         <label>Language</label>
         <input-type value-pairs-name="common_iso_languages">dropdown</input-type>
         <hint>Select the language of the main content of the item.  If the language does not appear in the list, please select 'Other'.  If the content does not really have a language (for example, if it is a dataset or an image) please select 'N/A'.</hint>
         <required></required>
       </field>

     </page>
